vectorData.altText: 23. The ______ _______ nerve is associated with dorsiflexion of the talocrural joint, inversion of the foot, and extension of the toes.

That's right!  The deep fibular nerve innervates muscles of the anterior compartment of the leg. Hence, it is responsible for dorsiflexion of the talocrural joint, inversion of foot and extension of toes.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
